mods.abstract: The recording is of a variety of live shows from the Grand Ole Opry. The recordings feature artist performances by: the Osborne Brothers (musical group), Jimmy Wilson (musician), Benny Martin (musical), Roy Acuff (musical), Bill Anderson (musician), Stringbean (musician), Bobby Bare (musician), and Jimmy C. Newman (musician). The first show is from November 27, 1965. The Luzianne show is from January 29, 1966. The remaining recordings are from a group of unidentified dates. The tape is labeled the third of thirteen.
